From: The Cinder Project <cinder@emberbrowser.org>
Subject: [PATCH 03/04] Configure DuckDuckGo as default search engine

Set DuckDuckGo as the default and only built-in search engine.
No other search engines are added without explicit user action.

Changes:
- Set DDG as default in search provider config
- Remove Google search provider definition
- Add DDG search URL template with %s placeholder
- Remove search suggestion endpoint for Google
- Configure instant search to off by default
---
 components/search_engines/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc | 30 +++++++++-----
 chrome/browser/search/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc    | 12 ++++
 2 files changed, 30 insertions(+), 12 deletions(-)

diff --git a/components/search_engines/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc b/components/search_engines/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc
index abc1234..def5678 100644
--- a/components/search_engines/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc
+++ b/components/search_engines/template_url_prepopulate_data.cc
@@ -1,30 +1,30 @@
-// EMBER: Search engine defaults overridden
-// DuckDuckGo is the sole default search engine.
+// Ember Browser: Search engine defaults overridden.
+// DuckDuckGo is the sole built-in search engine.
 
 const TemplateURLPrepopulateData::KeywordData kDefaultSearchProviderData = {
-    // Google (removed)
+    // DuckDuckGo
     .short_name = u"DuckDuckGo",
-    .keyword = u"duckduckgo.com",
+    .keyword = u"ddg",
     .search_url = u"https://duckduckgo.com/?q={searchTerms}",
     .suggest_url = u"https://duckduckgo.com/ac/?q={searchTerms}&type=list",
     .favicon_url = u"https://duckduckgo.com/favicon.ico",
     .new_tab_url = u"https://duckduckgo.com/",
 };
 
-// EMBER: No other search engines prepopulated
+// Ember: No other search engines prepopulated.
 // Users can add custom engines via ember.toml.
--
